1180–1236","1100–Male":"1100–Deceased","1236":"1236","Abt 1210":"about 1210","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","1210":"1210","1180":"1180","Merton, Norfolk, England":"Merton, Norfolk, England","London, England":"London, England, United Kingdom","Merton Manor, Norfolk, England":"Merton, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Baynard","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from the Middle English personal name <i>Bainard</i>, via Norman French from ancient Germanic <i>Beinhard</i>, perhaps from <i>bein-</i> ‘leg, bone’ or a supposed element <i>bagin-</i> ‘dispute’ + <i>-hard</i> ‘hard, brave’."],"variants":[{"name":"Bainer","meanings":["English: perhaps a late development of   Baynard  , with loss of the final <i>d</i>. The earliest record found of this name in Britain, spelled <i>Bayner</i>, is dated 1546."]},{"name":"Bunyard","meanings":["English (Kent, of Norman origin): variant of   Baynard  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Baynard was born in 1155, in Merton, Norfolk, England as the son of Ralph Baynard and Unknown. He had at least 1 daughter with Beatrice Beauchamp. He died about 1210, in London, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 56."},"et":{"1155–Abt 1210":"1155–umbes 1210","1155–1210":"1155–1210","–Female":"Surnud","1180–1236":"1180–1236","1100–Male":"1100–Surnud","1236":"1236","Abt 1210":"umbes 1210","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","1210":"1210","1180":"1180","Merton, Norfolk, England":"Merton, Norfolk, England","London, England":"London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Merton Manor, Norfolk, England":"Merton, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1155–Abt 1210":"1155–noin 1210","1155–1210":"1155–1210","–Female":"Kuollut","1180–1236":"1180–1236","1100–Male":"1100–Kuollut","1236":"1236","Abt 1210":"noin 1210","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","1210":"1210","1180":"1180","Merton, Norfolk, England":"Merton, Norfolk, England","London, England":"London, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Merton Manor, Norfolk, England":"Merton, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1155–Abt 1210":"1155–environ 1210","1155–1210":"1155–1210","–Female":"Décédée","1180–1236":"1180–1236","1100–Male":"1100–Décédé","1236":"1236","Abt 1210":"environ 1210","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","1210":"1210","1180":"1180","Merton, Norfolk, England":"Merton, Norfolk, Angleterre","London, England":"Londres, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Merton Manor, Norfolk, England":"Merton, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert Baynard est né en 1155, à Merton, Norfolk, Angleterre, fils de Ralph Baynard et Unknown. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Beatrice Beauchamp. Il est décédé environ 1210, à Londres, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 56 ans."},"de":{"1155–Abt 1210":"1155–um 1210","1155–1210":"1155–1210","–Female":"Verstorben","1180–1236":"1180–1236","1100–Male":"1100–Verstorben","1236":"1236","Abt 1210":"um 1210","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","1210":"1210","1